{
  "doc_id": "prion_0732",
  "text": "We describe a 68-year-old white woman who initially had symptoms of major depression and was admitted to a psychiatric hospital where she had electroconvulsive therapy.\nWith failure of psychiatric treatment and subsequent rapidly progressive dementia, she had left frontal brain biopsy.\nThe biopsy revealed spongiform changes, the hallmark of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD).\nWe report a case of sporadic CJD with unusual initial presentation of psychiatric symptoms.",
